1093:     /**
1094:      * This function is only called when sender is closed forcefully. It will fail all the
1095:      * incomplete batches and return.
1096:      */
1097:     public void abortIncompleteBatches() {
1098:         // We need to keep aborting the incomplete batch until no thread is trying to append to
1099:         // 1. Avoid losing batches.
1100:         // 2. Free up memory in case appending threads are blocked on buffer full.
1101:         // This is a tight loop but should be able to get through very quickly.
1102:         do {
1103:             abortBatches();
1104:         } while (appendsInProgress());
1105:         // After this point, no thread will append any messages because they will see the close
1106:         // flag set. We need to do the last abort after no thread was appending in case there was a new
1107:         // batch appended by the last appending thread.
1108:         abortBatches();
1109:         this.topicInfoMap.clear();
1110:     }
